      <guid>https://duragauge.github.io/chapter-1/1.1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div style=&#34;position:relative; clear:both; padding:0;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://duragauge.github.io/img/chapter-1/Smithsonian_wide.jpg&#34;  title=&#34;Smithsonian Museum of Natural History, photo by Blake Patterson&#34;  alt=&#34;Smithsonian Museum of Natural History, photo by Blake Patterson&#34; style=&#34;display:block; width:100%; height:auto;&#34; &gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;span style=&#34;position:absolute; height:auto; bottom:0em; right:0em; margin:0;  padding: .1em .3em;  color:white;  font-size: .8em;  background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);  text-align:right;  z-index:5;  opacity:0.65;  border-radius:.3em 0em 0em 0em;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;a href = &#34;https://www.flickr.com/photos/35448539@N00/8151668486&#34;&gt;Smithsonian Museum of Natural History, photo by Blake Patterson&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Smithsonian in Washington, DC is one of the largest museums in the world, housing vast collections of rare and historically significant objects.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
